**8.** A person has to pay 8% interest on the first Tk. 600 of his total expenses, and 7% interest on the amount exceeding Tk. 600. If his total expense in a year is Tk. 6000, how much interest does he have to pay that year?  
(IDAE (Store Keeper)-2017)  
- a. Tk. 480<br>  
- b. Tk. 420<br>  
- c. Tk. 378<br>  
- d. `Tk. 426`<br>  

+++ Solution:  
(6 × 8) + (54 × 7) = 426  
+++

